The real master tolerates misprints when reading history, as a good
traveller tolerates bad roads when climbing a mountain, one going to
watch a snow scene tolerates a flimsy bridge, one choosing to live in
the country tolerates vulgar people, and one bent on looking at
flowers tolerates bad wine.
